        <section>
            <h3>Project title: Library Management System Mini Project</h3>
            <p>The Library Management System mini project is a solution designed to streamline the day-to-day operations of a library.
                <dl>
                    <dt>Book Cataloging:</dt>
                    <dd>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Efficient cataloging of books with details such as title, author, genre, and ISBN.</li>
                            <li>Quick and easy addition of new books to the library inventory.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </dd>
                    <dt>Member Management:</dt>
                    <dd>
                        <ul>
                            <li>User-friendly member registration and management system.</li>
                            <li>Tracking of member details, including names, contact information, and borrowing history.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </dd>
                    <dt>Check-In/Check-Out:</dt>
                    <dd>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Smooth handling of book check-in and check-out processes.</li>
                            <li>Automated updates to the book status and member accounts.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </dd>
                    <dt>Search and Retrieval:</dt>
                    <dd>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Robust search functionality for books based on various parameters.</li>
                            <li>Quick retrieval of book availability status and location within the library.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </dd>
                    <dt>User Authentication:</dt>
                    <dd>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Secure login system for librarians and administrators.</li>
                            <li>Role-based access control to ensure data integrity and privacy.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </dd>
                </dl>
            </p>
        </section>
